    "Our insights enable renewing children's computing research and practice in several respects.",
    "We will continue tackling wicked societal problems of interest to children, collaboratively with them exploring the potential of AI/ML systems for social good.",
    "Current AIML curricula are primarily designed for STEM classrooms with AI concepts, practical applications and ethical implications as the primary goal (Casal-Otero, et al., 2023).",
    "However, AI literacy today is relevant to non-technical classrooms, and is not just a technical skill, but a socio-technical skill (Ali et al., 2021).",
    "Diverse fields of work such as art, law, education, policy, and sports are all impacted by AI."
